snippet.title: Beat the BBM iPhone and Android queue with this handy tip
snippet.description: The BlackBerry Messenger app on your iPhone or Android phone is finally out -- click here for the official link to download the BBM app.

snippet.title: Roku 1
snippet.description: The Roku 1 offers the same excellent experience that's found on other Roku boxes at a new low price, but there aren't many reasons to choose it over the new Streaming Stick or step-up Roku boxes.

snippet.title: G-Project G-Boom
snippet.description: For $100 you'll be hard-pressed to find another portable Bluetooth speaker that delivers as much bass as the G-Boom.

snippet.title: Braven BRV-1
snippet.description: If you're looking for a compact rugged, water-resistant Bluetooth speaker, the Braven BRV-1 is worth considering now that its street price has dropped to closer to $100.

snippet.title: Nikon 1 J4
snippet.description: The company announced its newest interchangeable-lens model everywhere but the US.

snippet.title: LG G Flex
snippet.description: Despite a novel construction and scuff-proof exterior, the LG G Flex's doesn't flex enough muscle against the Samsung Galaxy Round or the Note 3.

snippet.title: LG G Pro 2
snippet.description: The LG G Pro 2 delivers plenty of power, a huge and lovely screen, and a feature-packed camera, but the Galaxy Note 3's stylus and superior styling give it the edge.

snippet.title: LG G Pad 8.3
snippet.description: With its speedy and reliable performance, the LG G Pad 8.3 is a solid small-sized tablet, but for non-Verizon customers, the smoother and less expensive Google Nexus 7 is the better choice.
